<HL>
   Sharon Steel to Pay Penalty
</HL>
<DATE>
05/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A14
</SO>
<CO>
   SSH
</CO>
<IN>
ENVIRONMENT (ENV)
</IN>
<GV>
ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION AGENCY (EPA)
</GV>
<LP>
   PITTSBURGH -- Sharon Steel Corp. agreed to upgrade its
waste-water treatment facilities in western Pennsylvania and
to pay a $500,000 penalty for violating federal and state
clean-water laws.
   Under the terms of the settlement, announced by the
Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Resources, Sharon
Steel will complete construction of new waste-water treatment
facilities to lower its discharge of solid wastes into the
Shenango River.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The federal consent decree also requires Sharon to pay
civil penalties of $300,000 to the Department of
Environmental Protection and $200,000 to the Pennsylvania
state agency, for deposit in the state Clean Water Fund.
</TEXT>
